          "statement": "For which vectors $\\mathbf{b}$ does $A\\mathbf{x} = \\mathbf{b}$ have a solution when $A = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 2 \\\\ 2 & 4 \\end{pmatrix}$?",
          "solution": "The columns of $A$ are $(1, 2)$ and $(2, 4) = 2(1, 2)$. They are parallel, spanning only the line through $(1, 2)$. So $A\\mathbf{x} = \\mathbf{b}$ has a solution iff $\\mathbf{b}$ is a multiple of $(1, 2)$, i.e., $\\mathbf{b} = c(1, 2)$ for some scalar $c$."
